      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Except for cysteine, only <i>S</i> amino acids occur in proteins. Several <i>R</i> amino acids are also found in nature, however. (<i>R</i>)-Serine is found in earthworms, and (<i>R</i>)-alanine is found in insect larvae. Draw Fischer projections of (<i>R</i>)-serine and (<i>R</i>)-alanine. Are these <small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small> or <small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">L</small> amino acids?",
